column1: instructions1

You're now almost finished the task! In the last part, you will do another memory test. You will be shown an image, like below, on each trial. Your job is to indicate whether you have seen this image before at ANY point in the task. If you have seen the image before, press 'f' to indicate that it is old. If you haven't seen this image before, press 'j' to indicate the image is new.
Since you have seen the book before, you should select 'f' to indicate the book is old.
This test is timed. You have a limit of 2 seconds to respond. So try to respond as quickly as possible.
First we will do a practice. When you’re ready to start the practice, press the space bar.
There are now only a few more questions left! Please press space to continue.

During the task, you first learned image pairs. For example, you learned that the book was paired with the woman. Later, you saw an old image (e.g., the book) with a new second image (e.g., the alpaca) and you decided whether the images weighed more than a small dog.
column2: IN GENERAL, during the small dog task, when you saw an old image with a new pair, did you recall the earlier image pair (e.g., the woman)? Press 'N' if you did not recall the earlier image pair, press 'T' if you were actively trying to recall the earlier image pair, press 'P' if the earlier image pair popped into mind without you trying.

column1: Did you think about the earlier image pair when you FIRST saw the new pair, or during the arrow task, or both? Press 'J' if you thought about the earlier image pair when you first encountered  the new pair. Press 'K' if you mostly thought the earlier image pair during the arrow task. Press 'L' if the answer is both.

What proportion of the arrow task were you thinking about the earlier image pairs after seeing the new image pair on a scale of 1 to 7. With 1 being no time at all, 4 being half the time, and 7 being the entire time.
How bored were you during the arrow task? Please rate your boredom on a scale of 1 to 7. With 1 being not bored at all, 4 being neutral, and 7 being completely bored.
How interested were you in the task? Please rate your interest on a scale of 1 to 7, with 1 being not interested at all, 4 being neutral, and 7 being very interested.

How often did your mind drift away during the arrow task to your other daily concerns or daydreams? Please rate how often you engaged in internal thinking and mind wandering on a scale of 1 to 7. With 1 being not at mind wandering and totally focused on the task, 4 being sometimes daydreaming and thinking about other concerns, and 7 being daydreaming and/or thinking about other concerns the majority of the time.

How motivated were you to do well on the memory task? Please rate your motivation on a scale of 1 to 7, with 1 being not motivated at all, 4 being a kind of motivated and 7 being very motivated to do well on the memory task.
How much stress did you experience this week? Please rate the stres you experienced on a scale of 1 to 7, with 1 being no stress, 4 being some stress, and 7 being a lot of stress.

How often did you think about your stressful experiences during the arrow task? Please rate how often you thought about stressful events on a scale of 1 to 7, with 1 being not at all, 4 being sometimes, and 7 being most of the time.
How often do you use social media? Please rate how many hours per day you spend on social media rounded to the nearest hour. Please use the keys

How many hours per day do you spend either on facebook, checking your phone, or on instagram or other social and social media applications? Using the keys 1 to 9 to make a response, with 1 being 1 hour and 9 being 9 hours, approximately.
How aroused do you feel right now? With 1 being not aroused and sleepy, 4 being neutral, and 7 being very aroused.

This ladder represents how well off people in your community are with 9 being the most well off and 0 being the least well off. Which rung do you think you are on this ladder? Use the numbers 0 to 9 to make a response.
Thank you for completing this task! You are now finished.
